n style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> training services and disseminate information and research. We develop partnerships to enable us to work on new initiatives and projects to support the public’s health and create new education and training opportunities for the wider workforce.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">During 20</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">11-12, The RSPH, along with other independent organisations, Royal Colleges and charities participated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in a number of groups, initiated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by the Department of Health </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to provide advice and guidance about the transition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> plans for the move of public health from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the National Health Service to its</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> new base in Local Authorities in England.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The RSPH is a firm supporter of the move of public health from the NHS to local authorities where we believe there is a great opportunity to integrate and promote health and wel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lbeing across all local authority services. Extending the remit of improving health across the broader services will help to ensure that responsibilities for health and well being are integrated across communities. The RSPH is a supporter of the developmen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t of Public Health England and its role in enabling and supporting local authorities to create healthier communities.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Health England was established on April 1, 2013 and has only been operating for 7 months, but in that time we believe that the org</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">anisation has made a significant mark on the public health landscape</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There has been clear and strong leadership from the Chief Executive and his senior team about the role and priorities of Public Health England. They have communicated regularly both in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ternally and externally about the priorities and about their activities. The leadership team has created a positive and ‘learning’ culture in the organisation, which we have experienced in staff across the country.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> This has created the impression of a ‘can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> do’ organisation.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Health England has made significant efforts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> over the last seven months </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to engage stakeholders in different sectors so that they have a broad base of support an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d advice from expert organisations and individuals across the country. This is a difficult and time consuming task but one which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they have taken on i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n various aspects of their work</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by developing numerous task and advisory groups on specific subjects.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Publ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ic Health </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">England </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has been actively listening to the views and voices of other people and organisations and has been inclusive in their work practices.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As a new organisation, PHE has supported collaborative working and partnerships and the staff have made</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> efforts to take a joined up approach to public health. Their vision has been to encourage and foster a more integrated and broader approach to improving the public’s health.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Health England has made an excellent start in articulating the overarchin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">g vision for public health and what the changes will mean in practice. As an organisation, it has also been clear about its enabling role with local authorities and supporting local decision making about health and wellbeing. The organisation has indicated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> how and where to find expert support and guidance at all levels and senior staff has been very visible in all parts of England, visiting regional offices, local authorities and local projects</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Providing the evidence base to develop local priorities in pu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">blic health and disseminating best practice in interventions and collaborations is an important part of PHE’s role and they have made a good start in developing and c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ommunicating the evidence base and the need to develop the evidence in different areas .Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ey will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> need to continue to liaise and work with other organisations to ensure that they capture and share what works in varying locations.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They have been liaising with partners to discuss the capture and dissemination of evidence and it is clear that this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a priority for them.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">With the creation of Public Health England and the delegation of responsibility of public health t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o local authorities, there is an opportunity to develop the public health system to include individuals, employers in all sectors an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d community organisations. The more informed the general public is about preventing ill health and understanding their own health and wellbeing, the more successful the outcomes for population health. We expect that in this new environment, with PHE leader</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ship, more people in communities will gain the knowledge, training and confidence to promote health and well being. We support their priority for a Skills Passport as a vehicle to underpin a more flexible, broader and skilled workforce.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Although this is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">early days for Public Health England, at the RSPH we believe that they have made an excellent start and we look forward to working with the organisation to improve health and wellbeing in England.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">October</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-heigh